<heading id="D0AD4C27151C5A05FCB80CB9FA4D887A" box="[813,1448,1787,1811]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B92E2759151C5A05FCB80CB9FBC2887A" box="[813,1063,1787,1811]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80C8151C5A05FCB80CB9FBC2887A" box="[813,1063,1787,1811]" class="Erysipelotrichi" family="Erysipelotrichaceae" genus="Erysipelothrix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Erysipelotrichales" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="inopinata">Erysipelothrix inopinata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(in.o.pi.na'ta. L. fem. adj. 
<emphasis id="B92E2759151C5A05FAD10CB9FA4D887A" box="[1348,1448,1787,1811]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">inopinata</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5FB4B151C5A05FCB80D58FC5C885B" box="[813,953,1818,1842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<heading id="D0AD4C27151C5A05FCB80D58FC5C885B" box="[813,953,1818,1842]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" reason="1">unexpected).</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5FB4B151C5A05FCB80D0DFA4D880E" box="[813,1448,1871,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<heading id="D0AD4C27151C5A05FCB80D0DFA4D880E" box="[813,1448,1871,1895]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" reason="1">Cells are Gram-positive, catalase- and oxidase-negative,</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5FB4B151C5A05FCB80D2FFA4D88EF" box="[813,1448,1901,1926]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<heading id="D0AD4C27151C5A05FCB80D2FFA4D88EF" box="[813,1448,1901,1926]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" reason="1">non-motile, non-spore-forming rods, approximately 0·5 µm</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5FB4B151C5A05FCB80DCEFA4D88CD" box="[813,1448,1932,1956]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<heading id="D0AD4C27151C5A05FCB80DCEFA4D88CD" box="[813,1448,1932,1956]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="4" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" reason="1">in width and 1·5–3·0 µm in length. Surface colonies on</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5FB4B151B5A02FF1D0AF4FD388ECD" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">
BHI (Difco) after 2 days incubation are punctiform to approximately 1· 
<quantity id="4CA256AE151B5A02FED70A96FE618F84" box="[322,388,212,237]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
in diameter, creamy white, undulate, convex, translucent and soft. Growth occurs under aerobic and anaerobic conditions in BHI and columbia blood media, preferably at pH 8. Growth occurs at 20 and 40 °C, but not at 45 °C. The optimal temperature for growth is 25–30 °C. Physiological properties are indicated in 
<tableCitation id="C6D8CEF0151B5A02FF330BC9FF128ECD" box="[166,247,395,420]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="3.[110,174,184,205]" captionText="Table 1. Phenotypic properties that differentiate the novel isolate from Erysipelothrix strains, as determined by the API 32 STREPT and Biolog GP microplate panels" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">Table 1</tableCitation>
. DNA G+C content is 37·5 mol% (
<collectionCode id="ED4B638E151B5A02FD120BC9FD348ECD" box="[647,721,395,420]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">HPLC</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
